spanGrp.span: iidu gabalagw wazazeeden aa qafk law
I came to grow up here in Law
bat qawuuy hud aa abeet gesarmanay shandal
When I was I girl, we were dancing the shandala dance
Wakati nimekuwa Binti tukawa tunacheza ngoma (shandala)
nyiis geway aa qareemang aa geb eaarmani
Often we would go with the men and we would dance
Huwa tunaenda na wanaume na tunaenda kucheza
Then we would return home to eat
anin bad gaheedoj gequs gicha eeng'enani
When I was about to marry
Later I married into a tribe
bad gogenan nadeeg gaftadeej ab hoshu a idu aa gedilay giyeet gabigooj quwar gand quwar anin qawasch asimjaanda
When I married into a tribe, then when I would return home I would be at home and now I was Asimjeeg
Wakati nimeolewa na makabila nikawa nimerudi nyumbani nipo nyumbani sasa mimi ni mwaasimjega
gwayd sijilanan gejilan mwaka sabini na sita
wazazeedeny gabalagw qang'eedeew mang'ola aa qafk hiji
My parents came from Mang'ola to here
'Wazazi wangu wakatoka mang''ola na kuja huku'
I studied at school until year...
Nikasoma shuleni na kufika mwaka wa
aa gand law hanan hiji jeed asimjeeg gaheed asimjeeg qada aang'ayii
I was in Law here with the Asimjeeg, but the Asimjeeg are very few
Na nilikuwa Musoma hapo ndani ya waasimjeega nilikulia lakini waasimjeega ni wachache
There isn't an Asimjeeg person that we don't get along with
Hakuna mwasimjeega ambao hatuna undugu nao
asimjeeg anin ga anal hanan su mid law hijiini
The Asimjeeg that I know are these who are here in Law
Waasimjega ambao mimi nawafahamu ni hao ambao wapo hapo Musoma
Even the east, I have reached that area, I don't know them
ganalay su mid law su gayiinyay gwand ga mid bunda
I know those who are in Law, and I heard there are others in Bunda
Nawafahamu hao ambao wapo musoma wengine nasiki wapo Bunda
seen ga bund manali qanal au sind hij gichay aa gedufch seen
Those in Bunda I don't know them, I know only those here, and we all know each other.
Wa Bunda siwafahamu mimi najua hao ambao tupo hapo na tuna undugu wote
upandeed qamatenu aa upndeed qondeen upandeed qondeed gewasch qay eed haw gwand mang'ol eed haw
On my mother's side and on my father's side, on my father side we are veru few in Law, many are in Mang'ola
'Upande wa mama yangu na upande baba yangu upande wa baba yangu tupo wachache Musoma wengi wao wapo Mang''ola '
ga sind hiij upandeed qamateenu ga saw qay sijil law hiji
Those that are here are my mom's side, they were born here in Law
Tuliopo hapo ni upande wa mama yangu wao walizaliwa hapo Musoma
ar jajiidany hanan gamews hij ba lawuun
Even our grandfather he passed away here in Law
Hata babu wetu alifariki hapo Musoma
aa asees geng'eedeew mang'ol qahany geng'edeew mang'ol
And we we came from our home in Mang'ola, we came from Mang'ola
'Na sisi tulitoka mang''ola kwetu tulitoka Mang''ola'
qondeen gejil hanan gayeew hosh aa qon qaqeen qamateen ab law hiji
My father he was born in the east, and came to marry my mother here in Musoma
Baba yangu alizaliwa mashariki huko na akaja kumwoa mama yangu hapo Musoma
